# Backend Service Patterns

## Adding a new service to the pipeline

1. Create `backend/app/services/alphasignal/my_service.py`.
2. Define a class with `__init__(self, settings: Settings | None = None)`.
3. Wrap public methods with `@traceable_step("descriptive_step_name")`.
4. Wire into `AlphaSignalAgent` in `agent.py` via constructor injection (so tests can mock it).
5. Add the corresponding Pydantic schema to `shared/schemas/alphasignal.py` if new data types are needed.

## AlphaSignal client

```python
archive_json = self.alphasignal.fetch_archive_listing()
newsletter_html = self.alphasignal.fetch_newsletter_content(entry.url)
```

## PublicationMemory (dedup)

```python
memory = PublicationMemory(db)
unseen = memory.find_latest_unseen(archive_entries)  # returns ArchiveEntry | None
if unseen:
    # ... process ...
    memory.mark_seen(unseen)
```

Dedup key is a SHA-256 of `url|title|published_at`; collision-safe across restarts.

## Newsletter parsing

`parse_newsletter(archive_entry, content)` handles both HTML and plain text.
It returns a `NewsletterDigest` with `.highlights` and `.detailed_items`.
Each `NewsItem` has `.title`, `.summary`, `.detail_url`, `.section`.

## LangSmith tracing

`configure_langsmith(settings)` must be called once per run (already done inside `AlphaSignalAgent.run()`).
All `@traceable_step` decorators are no-ops when `langsmith` is not installed.

## Injecting services in tests

```python
agent = AlphaSignalAgent(
    db=db_session,
    alphasignal_client=mock_alphasignal,
    summarizer=mock_summarizer,
    email_sender=mock_email,
)
result = agent.run()
```
